  Systemd.service(5) - System and service manager
  Systemd.service(5)

  1. Description

  Systemd is a system and service manager for Linux, compatible with
  SysV and LSB init scripts. systemd provides aggressive parallelism
  and uses the Linux kernel's dependency and watchdog features for
  out-of-memory and process failure handling. systemd is well suited
  as a system and service manager for Linux,
